## Testing plan

Gates that apply to this slice (run in order; first failure short-circuits):
`build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `impl-log-structure`,
`state-of-world-structure`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`.

- `ui-tests`: a fit-page headless view test asserts Start dispatches the run, the
  per-iteration `progressText` updates via marshaled `ReportProgress`, completion
  refreshes the charts via `FitCompleted` with no manual reload (AC-U7.1), Cancel
  stops cooperatively with Revert available (AC-U7.2), and Accept replaces the
  working system only after `acceptConfirmationPrompt`, with Accept/Revert/Cancel
  same-row (AC-U7.3).
- `ui-smoke`: the fit page renders one frame headlessly.
- `build`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `unit-tests`: green; no frozen edits.

## Risks

- **High: threading-sensitive.** This is the only long-running background job in
  the arc. Every progress/completion dispatch from the run loop MUST marshal onto
  the UI thread via `Dispatcher.UIThread.Post` (§0.4); the `CancellationTokenSource`
  and run/progress state MUST live outside the root model (§0.5); cooperative
  cancellation MUST resolve to `Fit (FitFailed "cancelled")` and leave the prior
  committed results intact. A direct cross-thread dispatch or a duplicated
  run-state copy in the root model is a defect.

## Hand-off

- The fit page reuses the §0.4 marshaling discipline established by slice 003's
  node-solve `Cmd`; the comparison overlay reuses the slice-002 `AvaPlot` host.
- Emit the state-of-the-world `gates:` YAML block with this round's baseline
  counts so the next (final) slice's `count_at_least` gates have a baseline.
